BLUETONGUE, CATTLE - SPAIN (ANDALUCIA): OIE
*******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 15 Oct 2004
From: Pablo Nart<p.nart@ntlworld.com>
Source: Office International des Epizooties (OIE), Alert Messages [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/Messages/041014ESP.htm>

Bluetongue in Spain -- in the peninsular territory
<http://www.oie.int/eng/en_index.htm>
(Date of previous outbreak of bluetongue in Spain reported to the
OIE: December 2003 [in the Balearic Islands]).
Translation of information received on 14 Oct 2004 from Dr Arnaldo
Cabello Navarro, Deputy Director General of Animal Health, Ministry
of Agriculture, Fisheries and Food, Madrid:
Date of the report: 14 Oct 2004.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 4 Oct 2004.
Estimated date of primary infection: 30 Sep 2004.
Date of confirmation of diagnosis: 12 Oct 2004.
Outbreak: one farm in Jimena de la Frontera municipality, Cadiz
province, Andalucia Autonomous Community. The affected farm is 600 m
from any other farm containing susceptible animals.
Total number of animals in the outbreak: 695 bovines. Stamping-out
operations are due to be completed on 15 Oct 2004.
Source of agent / origin of infection: unknown.
Control measures: adoption of measures in accordance with the Royal
Decree No. 1228/2001 dated 8 Nov 2001, laying down specific control
and eradication measures for bluetongue, and with Animal Health Act
No. 8/2003 dated 24 Apr 2003.
